-They're firing another!
-All power to forward shields!

28
00:02:49,560 --> 00:02:50,720
Lieutenant!

29
00:02:55,760 --> 00:02:57,200
Atmospheric stabilisation has been lost.

30
00:02:57,480 --> 00:02:59,130
-Were our shields even up?
-Oxygen failing, Decks 7 to 13.

31
00:02:59,440 --> 00:03:01,050
-We have confirmed casualties, sir.
-Shields 11% and dropping.

32
00:03:01,360 --> 00:03:02,620
Ten percent. Shields at nine.
We're dropping here.

33
00:03:02,880 --> 00:03:06,570
All remaining power to forward shields.
Prepare shuttles for evacuation.

34
00:03:09,120 --> 00:03:10,100
Hello.

35
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:13,640
My commander requests
the presence of your Captain

36
00:03:14,040 --> 00:03:16,040
in order to negotiate a cease-fire.

37
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:18,860
You will come aboard our ship
via shuttlecraft.

38
00:03:19,280 --> 00:03:21,530
Your refusal would be unwise.

39
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:35,220
Walk with me.

40
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:43,860
If l don't report in 15 minutes,
evacuate the crew.

41
00:03:44,320 --> 00:03:46,600
-Sir, we could issue...
-There is no help for us out here.

42
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:48,230
Use autopilot.

43
00:03:49,680 --> 00:03:51,680
-And get off this ship.
-Aye, Captain.

44
00:03:52,040 --> 00:03:53,900
You're Captain now, Mr Kirk.

45
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:05,960
His heart rate’s elevated.

46
00:05:27,640 --> 00:05:29,080
Look at this ship.

47
00:05:30,960 --> 00:05:34,049
-Are you familiar with this craft?
-Who is your commander?

48
