Get to it now. Can you do that?

67
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:13,610
-Yes.
-Everything’s gonna be okay.

68
00:07:13,880 --> 00:07:17,320
-Do exactly as I say. Shuttle 37.
-George, it's coming.

69
00:07:17,880 --> 00:07:20,550
-Our baby, it's coming now.
-I’m on my way.

70
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:28,680
Autopilot function has been destroyed.

71
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:30,910
Manual operation only.

72
00:07:32,080 --> 00:07:34,219
Clear those decks now!
Get to the shuttles! Move, move, move!

73
00:07:34,600 --> 00:07:37,300
Get to the hangar deck!
Get to the hangar deck! Let's move it!

74
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:41,570
-That was a big one.
-Just keep breathing. You'll be fine.

75
00:07:41,960 --> 00:07:44,310
-And the baby, too, right?
-And the baby, too.

76
00:07:49,680 --> 00:07:51,680
Right here. Go ahead and sit back.

77
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:58,070
Captain to shuttle 37.
Is my wife onboard?

78
00:07:58,440 --> 00:08:00,690
-Yes, sir, she is.
-I need you to go now. Do you hear me?

79
00:08:01,080 --> 00:08:03,250
-We're waiting on you, sir.
-No, just go. Take off immediately.

80
00:08:03,960 --> 00:08:05,539
-That's an order.
-Yes, sir.

81
00:08:05,960 --> 00:08:07,400
No, wait! We can't go yet!

82
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:12,500
Please stop! Stop!

83
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:16,930
George? The shuttle's leaving.
Where are you?

84
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:18,730
Sweetheart, listen to me.

85
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:21,300
I’m not gonna be there.

86
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:23,420
-No.
-This is the only way you'll survive.

87
00:08:23,760 --> 00:08:26,010
Are you still on the ship?
You have to be here!

88
00:08:26,400 --> 00:08:28,190
The shuttles will never make it
if l don't fight them off.

89
00:08:28,520 --> 00:08:31,080
George, I can't do this without you.

90
00:08:31,520 --> 00:08:33,520
Okay, I need you to push now.

91
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:49,570
-What is it?
-It's a boy.

92
00:09:50,080 --> 00:09:51,090
A boy?

93
00:09:52,600 --> 00:09:53,720
Tell me about him.

94
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:56,200
He's beautiful.

95
00:09:58,360 --> 00:09:59,730
George, you should be here.

96
00:10:01,480 --> 00:10:02,740
Impact alert.

97
00:10:04,920 --> 00:10:07,900
-What are we gonna call him?
-We can name him after your father.

98
00:10:08,720 --> 00:10:11,320
"Tiberius"? You kidding me?
No, that's the worst.

99
00:10:13,480 --> 00:10:16,010
Let's name him after your dad.
Let's call him Jim.

100
00:10:18,400 --> 00:10:21,240
Jim. Okay. Jim it is.

101
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:28,000
-Sweetheart, can you hear me?
-l hear you!

102
00:10:28,360 --> 00:10:31,450
I love you so much. I love you...

103
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:48,650
Hey, are you out of your mind?
That car is an antique.

104
00:11:48,960 --> 00:11:51,130
You think you can get away with this
just ‘cause your mother’s off planet?

105
00:11:51,520 --> 00:11:53,520
You get your ass back home now!

106
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:56,970
You live in my house, buddy.
You live in my house, and that’s my car.

107
00:11:57,480 --> 00:11:59,900
You get one scratch on that car,
and I'm gonna whip your...

108
00:12:12,920 --> 00:12:14,180
Yeah!

109
00:12:23,480 --> 00:12:24,640
Hey, Johnny!

110
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:45,910
Citizen! Pull over.

111
00:13:11,680 --> 00:13:13,290
No!

112
00:13:38,360 --> 00:13:40,180
Is there a problem, Officer?

113
00:13:40,920 --> 00:13:42,740
Citizen, what is your name?

114
00:13:43,480 --> 00:13:45,370
My name is James Tiberius Kirk.

115
00:14:03,240 --> 00:14:05,410
What is the formula
for the volume of a sphere?

116
00:14:05,800 --> 00:14:08,010
Four-thirds pi times the radius cubed.

117
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:09,510
One-point-two-six.

118
00:14:09,720 --> 00:14:10,590
An ellipse.

119
00:14:10,800 --> 00:14:12,339
What is the electrical charge
of an up-type quark?

120
00:14:12,640 --> 00:14:14,150
Positive two-thirds.

121
00:14:14,440 --> 00:14:18,550
What is the square root of 2,396,324?

122
00:14:19,200 --> 00:14:20,780
-1,548.
-What is the dimensionality...

123
00:14:21,080 --> 00:14:23,360
Dimensionality equals the logarithm
and divided by...

124
00:14:23,760 --> 00:14:26,920
Non-excludability and non-rivalry...
Four-thirds pi times the radius cubed.

125
00:14:27,440 --> 00:14:30,560
When it is morally praiseworthy
but not morally obligatory.

126
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:34,970
Spock!

127
00:14:37,160 --> 00:14:39,719
I presume you've prepared
new insults for today.

128
00:14:40,440 --> 00:14:41,600
Affirmative.

129
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:52,690
This is your thirty-fifth attempt to elicit
an emotional response from me.

130
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:55,760
You're neither human nor Vulcan, and
therefore have no place in this universe.

131
00:14:56,200 --> 00:14:58,620
Look. He has human eyes.
They look sad, don't they?

132
00:14:59,040 --> 00:15:01,990
Perhaps an emotional response
requires physical stimuli.

133
00:15:03,920 --> 00:15:08,240
He's a traitor, you know. Your father.
For marrying her. That human whore.

134
00:15:36,280 --> 00:15:38,000
They called you a traitor.

135
00:15:42,840 --> 00:15:44,870
Emotions run deep within our race.

136
00:15:45,760 --> 00:15:48,220
In many ways,
more deeply than in humans.

137
00:15:48,640 --> 00:15:51,620
Logic offers a serenity
humans seldom experience.

138
00:15:52,480 --> 00:15:56,480
The control of feelings,
so that they do not control you.

139
00:16:00,040 --> 00:16:02,709
You suggest
that I should be completely Vulcan,

140
00:16:03,640 --> 00:16:05,430
and yet, you married a human.

141
00:16:05,760 --> 00:16:07,550
As ambassador to Earth, it is my duty

142
00:16:07,880 --> 00:16:10,200
to observe
and understand human behaviour.

143
00:16:11,040 --> 00:16:12,550
Marrying your mother was

144
00:16:14,200 --> 00:16:15,280
logical.

145
00:16:17,840 --> 00:16:21,950
Spock. You are fully capable
of deciding your own destiny.

146
00:16:23,800 --> 00:16:27,870
The question you face is,
which path will you choose?

147
00:16:29,840 --> 00:16:32,090
This is something only you can decide.

148
00:16:37,680 --> 00:16:40,000
Spock, come here, let me see you.

149
00:16:42,400 --> 00:16:44,500
-No.
-Spock.

150
00:16:52,360 --> 00:16:56,010
There's no need to be anxious.
You'll do fine.

151
00:16:56,760 --> 00:16:58,620
lam hardly anxious, Mother.

152
00:16:58,960 --> 00:17:02,120
And "fine" has variable definitions.
"Fine" is unacceptable.

153
00:17:03,400 --> 00:17:04,310
Okay.

154
00:17:11,800 --> 00:17:14,500
-May I ask a personal query?
-Anything.

155
00:17:17,480 --> 00:17:20,710
Should I choose to complete
the Vulcan discipline of Kolinahr

156
00:17:21,720 --> 00:17:23,370
and purge all emotion,

157
00:17:25,560 --> 00:17:28,369
I trust you will not feel
it reflects judgement upon you.

158
00:17:31,640 --> 00:17:32,760
Spock.

159
00:17:35,200 --> 00:17:38,080
As always, whatever you choose to be,

160
00:17:39,480 --> 00:17:41,370
you will have a proud mother.

161
00:17:45,960 --> 00:17:49,290
You have surpassed the expectations
of your instructors.

162
00:17:49,840 --> 00:17:53,100
Your final record is flawless,
with one exception.

163
00:17:53,920 --> 00:17:57,080
I see that you have applied
to Starfleet as well.

164
00:17:57,600 --> 00:17:59,600
It was logical
to cultivate multiple options.

165
00:17:59,960 --> 00:18:01,680
Logical, but unnecessary.

166
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:04,600
You are hereby accepted
to the Vulcan Science Academy.

167
00:18:05,040 --> 00:18:06,300
It is truly remarkable, Spock,

168
00:18:06,560 --> 00:18:09,370
that you have achieved so much
despite your disadvantage.

169
00:18:10,400 --> 00:18:11,520
All rise!

170
00:18:15,240 --> 00:18:17,200
If you would clarify, Minister,

171
00:18:18,360 --> 00:18:21,310
-to what disadvantage are you referring?
-Your human mother.

172
00:18:26,760 --> 00:18:29,290
Council. Ministers, ] must decline.

173
00:18:29,720 --> 00:18:32,000
No Vulcan has ever declined
admission to this Academy.

174
00:18:32,400 --> 00:18:34,720
Then as I am half human,
your record remains untarnished.

175
00:18:35,120 --> 00:18:38,239
Spock, you have made a commitment
to honour the Vulcan way.

176
00:18:38,760 --> 00:18:40,690
Why did you come
before this council today?

177
00:18:41,040 --> 00:18:43,210
Was it to satisfy
your emotional need to rebel?

178
00:18:43,600 --> 00:18:46,199
The only emotion I wish to convey
is gratitude.

179
00:18:47,520 --> 00:18:50,540
Thank you, Ministers,
for your consideration.

180
00:18:52,760 --> 00:18:54,340
Live long and prosper.

181
00:19:09,840 --> 00:19:10,889
-How are you?
-Hey.

182
00:19:15,320 --> 00:19:16,760
-Hi.
-Hi.

183
00:19:22,080 --> 00:19:26,790
Hi, I'd like a Klabnian Fire Tea,
three Budweiser Classics,

184
00:19:27,520 --> 00:19:30,820
-two Cardassian Sunrises and...
-Gotta try the Slusho. It's good.

185
00:19:31,360 --> 00:19:32,729
The Slusho mix. Thank you.

186
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:35,250
That's a lot of drinks for one woman.

187
00:19:37,040 --> 00:19:39,290
-And a shot of Jack, straight up.
-Make that two. Her shot's on me.

188
00:19:39,680 --> 00:19:41,540
Her shot's on her. Thanks but no thanks.

189
00:19:41,880 --> 00:19:43,350
Don't you want to at least
know my name

190
00:19:43,640 --> 00:19:44,900
before you completely reject me?

191
00:19:45,160 --> 00:19:47,760
-I'm fine without it.
-You are fine without it.

192
00:19:48,440 --> 00:19:50,020
It's Jim. Jim Kirk.

193
00:19:51,960 --> 00:19:55,050
If you don't tell me your name,
I'm gonna have to make one up.

194
00:19:55,800 --> 00:19:57,620
-It's Uhura.
-Uhura? No way!

195
00:19:57,960 --> 00:20:00,030
That's the name
I was gonna make up for you.

196
00:20:00,400 --> 00:20:02,400
-Uhura what?
-Just Uhura.

197
00:20:02,760 --> 00:20:04,090
They don't have last names
in your world?

198
00:20:04,360 --> 00:20:05,550
Uhura is my last name.

199
00:20:05,800 --> 00:20:08,470
Well, they don't have first names
in your world?

200
00:20:10,360 --> 00:20:11,340
Excuse me, buddy.

201
00:20:11,560 --> 00:20:14,159
So, you're a cadet, you're studying.
What's your focus?

202
00:20:14,600 --> 00:20:16,669
Xenolinguistics.
You have no idea what that means.

203
00:20:17,040 --> 00:20:21,010
The study of alien languages.
Morphology, phonology, syntax.

204
00:20:22,280 --> 00:20:24,530
It means you've got a talented tongue.

205
00:20:25,160 --> 00:20:26,600
I'm impressed.

206
00:20:26,880 --> 00:20:28,560
For a moment there,
I thought you were just a dumb hick

207
00:20:28,880 --> 00:20:33,020
-who only has sex with farm animals.
-Well, not only.

208
00:20:34,880 --> 00:20:36,770
This townie isn't bothering you, right?

209
00:20:37,120 --> 00:20:39,260
Beyond belief.
But it's nothing I can't handle.

210
00:20:39,640 --> 00:20:41,320
You could handle me.
That's an invitation.

211
00:20:41,640 --> 00:20:45,260
-Hey, you better mind your manners.
-Relax, cupcake. It was a joke.

212
00:20:45,840 --> 00:20:49,810
Hey, farm boy. Maybe you can't count,
but there are four of us and one of you.

213
00:20:50,440 --> 00:20:53,460
So get some more guys,
and then it'll be an even fight.

214
00:20:56,920 --> 00:20:58,290
Guys, stop it.

215
00:21:00,920 --> 00:21:01,970
Stop it!

216
00:21:22,840 --> 00:21:23,820
Enough!

217
00:21:31,360 --> 00:21:32,479
Guys, he’s had enough!

218
00:21:37,840 --> 00:21:39,379
Outside, all of you.

219
00:21:40,440 --> 00:21:41,810
-Now!
-Yes, sir!

220
00:21:42,480 --> 00:21:43,920
-He wouldn't even listen!
-I just bought a drink.

221
00:21:44,200 --> 00:21:45,780
-Can you believe this?
-It's not really fair.

222
00:21:46,080 --> 00:21:48,250
-Come on.
-You all right, son?

223
00:21:48,640 --> 00:21:51,030
You can whistle really loud,
you know that?

224
00:21:52,400 --> 00:21:54,430
You know, I couldn't believe it when
the bartender told me who you are.

225
00:21:54,800 --> 00:21:57,399
-And who am I, Captain Pike?
-Your father's son.

226
00:22:01,120 --> 00:22:02,520
Can I get another one?

227
00:22:02,800 --> 00:22:05,120
For my dissertation,
Il was assigned the U.S.S. Kelvin.

228
00:22:05,520 --> 00:22:09,030
Something I admired about your dad,
he didn't believe in no-win scenarios.

229
00:22:09,600 --> 00:22:10,830
He sure learned his lesson.

230
00:22:11,160 --> 00:22:12,460
Well, it depends
on how you define winning.

231
00:22:12,720 --> 00:22:14,610
-You're here, aren't you?
-Thanks.

232
00:22:14,960 --> 00:22:17,520
You know, that instinct to leap
without looking, that was his nature, too.

233
00:22:17,960 --> 00:22:19,920
And in my opinion,
it's something Starfleet's lost.

234
00:22:20,280 --> 00:22:22,740
-Why are you talking to me, man?
-'Cause I looked up your file

235
00:22:23,160 --> 00:22:25,370
while you were drooling on the floor.

236
00:22:25,760 --> 00:22:28,920
Your aptitude tests are off the charts.
So what is it?

237
00:22:29,440 --> 00:22:31,790
You like being the only genius-level
repeat-offender in the Midwest?

238
00:22:32,200 --> 00:22:33,670
Maybe I love it.

239
00:22:33,960 --> 00:22:37,080
So your dad dies. You can settle
for a less-than-ordinary life.

240
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:40,550
Or do you feel like you were meant
for something better?

241
00:22:41,280 --> 00:22:42,720
Something special?

242
00:22:44,880 --> 00:22:46,810
-Enlist in Starfleet.
-Enlist?

243
00:22:48,760 --> 00:22:50,760
You guys must be way down
on your recruiting quota for the month.

244
00:22:51,120 --> 00:22:54,669
If you're half the man your father was,
Jim, Starfleet could use you.

245
00:22:55,640 --> 00:22:59,430
You can be an officer in four years.
You can have your own ship in eight.

246
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:03,129
You understand what the Federation is,
don't you? It's important.

247
00:23:03,560 --> 00:23:05,210
It's a peacekeeping
and humanitarian armada...

248
00:23:05,520 --> 00:23:07,980
-Are we done?
-I'm done.

249
00:23:13,160 --> 00:23:16,600
Riverside Shipyard. Shuttle for
new recruits leaves tomorrow, 0800.

250
00:23:20,840 --> 00:23:23,929
Now, your father was captain
of a starship for 12 minutes.

251
00:23:24,840 --> 00:23:28,840
He saved 800 lives,
including your mother's. And yours.

252
00:23:30,600 --> 00:23:32,250
I dare you to do better.

253
00:24:53,960 --> 00:24:55,150
Nice ride, man.

254
00:24:58,960 --> 00:25:00,150
It's yours.

255
00:25:00,960 --> 00:25:03,210
Four years? I'll do it in three.

256
00:25:18,560 --> 00:25:20,070
At ease, gentlemen.

257
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:41,150
-Never did get that first name.
-You need a doctor.

258
00:25:41,640 --> 00:25:43,430
I told you people, I don't need a doctor,
damn it, 1 am a doctor!

259
00:25:43,760 --> 00:25:44,629
You need to get back to your seat.

260
00:25:44,840 --> 00:25:45,750
l had one in the bathroom
with no windows.

261
00:25:45,960 --> 00:25:47,710
-You need to get back to your seat now.
-I suffer from aviaphobia.

262
00:25:48,040 --> 00:25:49,300
It means fear of dying
in something that flies.

263
00:25:49,560 --> 00:25:53,040
Sir, for your own safety, sit down,
or else I'll make you sit down!

264
00:25:55,520 --> 00:25:57,590
-Fine.
-Thank you.

265
00:25:58,560 --> 00:26:01,399
This is Captain Pike.
We've been cleared for takeoff.

266
00:26:02,040 --> 00:26:03,440
I may throw up on you.

267
00:26:03,720 --> 00:26:05,610
I think these things are pretty safe.

268
00:26:05,960 --> 00:26:07,990
Don't pander to me, kid.
One tiny crack in the hull

269
00:26:08,360 --> 00:26:10,290
and our blood boils in 13 seconds.

270
00:26:10,640 --> 00:26:13,060
A solar flare might crop up,
cook us in our seats.

271
00:26:13,480 --> 00:26:15,940
And wait till you're sitting pretty
with a case of Andorian shingles.

272
00:26:16,360 --> 00:26:19,169
See if you're still so relaxed
when your eyeballs are bleeding.

273
00:26:19,640 --> 00:26:22,660
Space is disease and danger
wrapped in darkness and silence.

274
00:26:23,160 --> 00:26:26,390
Well, I hate to break this to you,
but Starfleet operates in space.

275
00:26:26,920 --> 00:26:28,670
Yeah, well, I got nowhere else to go.

276
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:31,810
The ex-wife took the whole damn planet
in the divorce.

277
00:26:32,280 --> 00:26:34,030
All I got left is my bones.

278
00:26:39,480 --> 00:26:42,710
-Jim Kirk.
-McCoy. Leonard McCoy.

279
00:27:28,480 --> 00:27:31,600
Captain Nero! You've been
requested on the Bridge, sir.

280
00:27:32,120 --> 00:27:33,659
Ayel says it's time.

281
00:27:38,760 --> 00:27:43,260
Sir, we've arrived at the coordinates
you calculated. There's nothing here.

282
00:27:43,960 --> 00:27:45,890
-What are your orders?
-We wait.

283
00:27:46,880 --> 00:27:50,000
We wait for the one
who allowed our home to be destroyed,

284
00:27:50,520 --> 00:27:52,520
as we've been doing for 25 years.

285
00:27:54,040 --> 00:27:56,389
-And once we've killed him?
-Kill him?

286
00:27:57,080 --> 00:28:00,100
I'm not gonna kill him.
I'm gonna make him watch.

287
00:28:14,360 --> 00:28:15,479
Capture that ship!

288
00:28:17,240 --> 00:28:18,710
Welcome back, Spock.

289
00:28:22,840 --> 00:28:23,850
Why are you so happy?

290
00:28:24,080 --> 00:28:26,080
-I don't know what you're talking about.
-No, I don't suppose you do.

291
00:28:26,440 --> 00:28:27,700
Hello, ladies!

292
00:28:28,440 --> 00:28:29,840
-I'm taking the test again.
-You gotta be kidding.

293
00:28:30,120 --> 00:28:31,590
Yeah, tomorrow morning,
and I want you there.

294
00:28:31,880 --> 00:28:32,860
You know, I've got better things to do

295
00:28:33,080 --> 00:28:34,830
than watch you embarrass yourself
for a third time.

296
00:28:35,160 --> 00:28:36,350
I'm a doctor, Jim. I'm busy.

297
00:28:36,600 --> 00:28:38,530
Bones, it doesn't bother you
that no one's ever passed the test?

298
00:28:38,880 --> 00:28:41,130
Jim, it's the Kobayashi Maru.
No one passes the test.

299
00:28:41,520 --> 00:28:44,120
And no one goes back for seconds,
let alone thirds.

300
00:28:44,560 --> 00:28:45,820
I gotta study.

301
00:28:46,680 --> 00:28:48,080
Study, my ass.

302
00:28:48,480 --> 00:28:52,270
-Jim, I think I love you.
-That is so weird.

303
00:28:53,400 --> 00:28:54,870
-Lights.
-Lights on.

304
00:28:55,880 --> 00:28:57,180
Did you just say, "That is so weird"?

305
00:28:57,440 --> 00:28:59,190
-Yeah, I did, but...
-You don't love me, too?

306
00:28:59,520 --> 00:29:00,639
Oh, my God, my roommate!

307
00:29:00,880 --> 00:29:01,890
But I thought you said
she was gone for the night.

308
00:29:02,120 --> 00:29:03,699
Obviously she's not.
Quick, get under the bed.

309
00:29:04,000 --> 00:29:05,370
-Under...
-Look, just get under the bed.

310
00:29:05,640 --> 00:29:07,040
-Come on!
-She can't see you here.

311
00:29:07,320 --> 00:29:08,510
-Why not?
-Because I promised her

312
00:29:08,760 --> 00:29:09,810
-I'd stop bringing guys back to the room.
-Really?

313
00:29:10,040 --> 00:29:12,320
-Well, how many guys have you...
-Just down! Just down!

314
00:29:14,840 --> 00:29:15,709
-Hey.
-Hey.

315
00:29:15,920 --> 00:29:17,150
-How are you?
-Good.

316
00:29:17,400 --> 00:29:20,000
The strangest thing,
I was in the long-range sensor lab...

317
00:29:20,440 --> 00:29:21,950
Yeah, I thought all night.

318
00:29:22,240 --> 00:29:25,930
l was tracking solar systems and
I picked up an emergency transmission.

319
00:29:26,520 --> 00:29:29,610
-Really?
-Yeah. From a Klingon prison planet.

320
00:29:30,520 --> 00:29:31,460
-No.
-Yeah.

321
00:29:31,680 --> 00:29:33,820
A Klingon armada was destroyed.
Forty-seven ships.

322
00:29:34,200 --> 00:29:36,730
So you're not going back
to the lab tonight?

323
00:29:40,920 --> 00:29:42,320
-Gaila, who is he?
-Who's who?

324
00:29:42,600 --> 00:29:44,530
The mouth-breather
hiding under your bed.

325
00:29:44,880 --> 00:29:46,180
You could hear me breathing?

326
00:29:46,440 --> 00:29:47,770
-You!
-Big day tomorrow.

327
00:29:48,040 --> 00:29:50,320
-You're gonna fail. Get out.
-Gaila, see you around.

328
00:29:50,720 --> 00:29:51,950
If l pass,
will you tell me your first name?

329
00:29:52,200 --> 00:29:53,670
-No! Good night.
-I think the fact

330
00:29:53,960 --> 00:29:56,280
that you picked up a transmission
is very interesting.

331
00:29:58,480 --> 00:30:01,290
We are receiving a distress signal
from the U.S.S. Kobayashi Maru.

332
00:30:01,760 --> 00:30:03,410
The ship has lost power
and is stranded.

333
00:30:03,720 --> 00:30:05,330
Starfleet Command
has ordered us to rescue them.

334
00:30:05,640 --> 00:30:08,200
“Starfleet Command has ordered us
to rescue them,

335
00:30:09,720 --> 00:30:10,770
“Captain.”

336
00:30:11,800 --> 00:30:13,379
Two Klingon vessels
have entered the Neutral Zone

337
00:30:13,680 --> 00:30:16,030
-and are locking weapons on us.
-That's okay.

338
00:30:16,680 --> 00:30:18,750
-That's okay?
-Yeah, don’t worry about it.

339
00:30:19,400 --> 00:30:21,220
Did he say, "Don't worry about it"?

340
00:30:21,560 --> 00:30:23,100
Is he not taking
the simulation seriously?

341
00:30:23,600 --> 00:30:26,060
Three more Klingon warbirds decloaking
and targeting our ship.

342
00:30:26,480 --> 00:30:28,690
-I don't suppose this is a problem either.
-They're firing, Captain.

343
00:30:29,400 --> 00:30:31,650
Alert Medical Bay to prepare to receive
all crew members

344
00:30:32,040 --> 00:30:32,980
from the damaged ship.

345
00:30:33,200 --> 00:30:34,670
And how do you expect us
to rescue them

346
00:30:34,960 --> 00:30:37,240
when we're surrounded
by Klingons, Captain?

347
00:30:37,640 --> 00:30:38,900
Alert Medical.

348
00:30:41,280 --> 00:30:43,420
Our ship is being hit. Shields at 60%.

349
00:30:43,800 --> 00:30:45,550
-l understand.
-Well, should we, I don't know,

350
00:30:45,880 --> 00:30:47,140
fire back?

351
00:30:47,520 --> 00:30:49,100
-No.
-Of course not.

352
00:30:56,360 --> 00:30:58,250
What is this? What's going on?

353
00:31:01,920 --> 00:31:03,850
Arm photons.
Prepare to fire on the Klingon warbirds.

354
00:31:04,200 --> 00:31:06,020
-Yes, sir.
-Jim, their shields are still up.

355
00:31:06,360 --> 00:31:07,409
Are they?

356
00:31:09,200 --> 00:31:10,640
No. They're not.

357
00:31:11,320 --> 00:31:12,649
Fire on all enemy ships.

358
00:31:12,920 --> 00:31:15,170
One photon each should do.
Let's not waste ammunition.

359
00:31:15,560 --> 00:31:18,020
Target locked and acquired
on all warbirds. Firing.

360
00:31:23,240 --> 00:31:25,270
-All ships destroyed, Captain.
-Begin rescue of the stranded crew.

361
00:31:25,640 --> 00:31:28,760
So! We've managed to eliminate
all enemy ships,

362
00:31:29,280 --> 00:31:30,649
no one onboard was injured,

363
00:31:30,920 --> 00:31:35,450
and the successful rescue of the
Kobayashi Maru crew is underway.

364
00:31:40,400 --> 00:31:42,790
How the hell did that kid beat your test?

365
00:31:45,680 --> 00:31:46,940
I do not know.

366
00:31:48,120 --> 00:31:50,790
This session has been called
to resolve a troubling matter.

367
00:31:51,520 --> 00:31:53,310
James T. Kirk, step forward.

368
00:31:55,360 --> 00:31:57,709
Cadet Kirk, evidence has been
submitted to this council

369
00:31:58,120 --> 00:32:00,439
suggesting that you violated
the ethical code of conduct

370
00:32:00,840 --> 00:32:03,790
pursuant to Regulation 17.43
of the Starfleet code.

371
00:32:05,240 --> 00:32:08,190
Is there anything you care to say
before we begin, sir?

372
00:32:09,360 --> 00:32:12,550
Yes, I believe I have the right
to face my accuser directly.

373
00:32:16,920 --> 00:32:18,670
Step forward, please.

374
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:22,510
This is Commander Spock. He is one
of our most distinguished graduates.

375
00:32:23,080 --> 00:32:26,409
He's programmed the Kobayashi Maru
exam for the last four years.

376
00:32:28,520 --> 00:32:31,080
-Commander?
-Cadet Kirk, you somehow managed

377
00:32:31,520 --> 00:32:33,520
to install and activate a subroutine
in the programming code,

378
00:32:33,880 --> 00:32:36,300
thereby changing
the conditions of the test.

379
00:32:37,400 --> 00:32:40,380
-Your point being?
-In academic vernacular, you cheated.

380
00:32:42,520 --> 00:32:45,710
Let me ask you something
I think we all know the answer to.

381
00:32:46,680 --> 00:32:48,780
The test itself is a cheat, isn't it?

382
00:32:49,160 --> 00:32:50,770
I mean, you programmed it
to be unwinnable.

383
00:32:51,080 --> 00:32:53,250
Your argument precludes the possibility
of a no-win scenario.

384
00:32:53,640 --> 00:32:56,660
-I don't believe in no-win scenarios.
-Then not only did you violate the rules,

385
00:32:57,160 --> 00:32:58,810
you also failed to understand
the principal lesson.

386
00:32:59,120 --> 00:33:00,419
Please, enlighten me.

387
00:33:00,680 --> 00:33:02,540
You of all people should know,
Cadet Kirk,

388
00:33:02,880 --> 00:33:04,700
a captain cannot cheat death.

389
00:33:08,000 --> 00:33:09,050
I of all people?

390
00:33:09,280 --> 00:33:12,090
Your father, Lieutenant George Kirk,
assumed command of his vessel

391
00:33:12,560 --> 00:33:13,960
before being killed in action, did he not?

392
00:33:14,240 --> 00:33:15,750
I don't think you like the fact
that I beat your test.

393
00:33:16,040 --> 00:33:17,860
Furthermore, you have failed to divine
the purpose of the test.

394
00:33:18,200 --> 00:33:21,150
-Enlighten me again.
-The purpose is to experience fear,

395
00:33:22,400 --> 00:33:24,080
fear in the face of certain death.

396
00:33:24,400 --> 00:33:27,910
To accept that fear, and maintain
control of oneself and one's crew.

397
00:33:28,480 --> 00:33:31,360
This is a quality expected
in every Starfleet captain.

398
00:33:34,320 --> 00:33:35,439
Excuse me, sir.

399
00:33:41,880 --> 00:33:44,050
We've received a distress call
from Vulcan.

400
00:33:44,440 --> 00:33:47,040
With our primary fleet engaged
in the Laurentian system,

401
00:33:47,480 --> 00:33:51,200
I hereby order all cadets to report
to Hangar One immediately. Dismissed.

402
00:33:57,880 --> 00:34:01,360
-Who was that pointy-eared bastard?
-I don't know, but I like him.

403
00:34:05,920 --> 00:34:08,659
Fugeman, Regula One!
Gerace, U.S.S. Farragut!

404
00:34:09,120 --> 00:34:11,859
McCoy, U.S.S. Enterprise!
McGrath, U.S.S. Wolcott!

405
00:34:12,320 --> 00:34:15,300
Rader, U.S.S. Hood.
Welcome to Starfleet, and Godspeed.

406
00:34:17,880 --> 00:34:19,630
He didn't call my name.

407
00:34:20,560 --> 00:34:24,489
Commander? Sir, you didn't call
my name. Kirk, James T.

408
00:34:25,280 --> 00:34:26,470
Kirk, you're on academic suspension.

409
00:34:26,719 --> 00:34:29,139
That means you're grounded
until the Academy Board rules.

410
00:34:29,560 --> 00:34:31,909
All right, listen up! I'm gonna read
this list one time, and one time only!

411
00:34:33,040 --> 00:34:36,480
Jim, the Board will rule in your favour.
Most likely.

412
00:34:38,639 --> 00:34:41,589
-Look, Jim, I gotta go.
-Yeah.

413
00:34:42,280 --> 00:34:43,890
Yeah, you go. Be safe.

414
00:34:51,360 --> 00:34:53,250
-Excuse me.
-Yeah. Yeah. Sure.

415
00:34:58,160 --> 00:34:59,210
Damn it.

416
00:35:01,920 --> 00:35:04,800
-Come with me.
-U.S.S. Newton! Uhura, U.S.S. Farragut!

417
00:35:05,280 --> 00:35:08,440
Petrovsky, U.S.S. Antares!
Go to your stations and good luck.

418
00:35:12,160 --> 00:35:14,480
-Bones, where are we going?
-You'll see.

419
00:35:16,920 --> 00:35:18,290
-Commander, a word?
-Yes, Lieutenant?

420
00:35:18,560 --> 00:35:20,560
-Was I not one of your top students?
-Indeed you were.

421
00:35:20,920 --> 00:35:22,710
And did I not
on multiple occasions demonstrate

422
00:35:23,040 --> 00:35:25,710
an exceptional aural sensitivity
and, I quote,

423
00:35:26,160 --> 00:35:28,089
“an unparalleled ability
to identify sonic anomalies"

424
00:35:28,440 --> 00:35:31,280
-in subspace transmissions tests?
-Consistently, yes.

425
00:35:31,760 --> 00:35:33,440
And while you were well aware
that my unqualified desire

426
00:35:33,760 --> 00:35:36,320
is to serve on the U.S.S. Enterprise,
I'm assigned to the Farragut?

427
00:35:36,760 --> 00:35:39,430
It was an attempt to avoid
the appearance of favouritism.

428
00:35:39,880 --> 00:35:41,980
No. I'm assigned to the Enterprise.

429
00:35:46,320 --> 00:35:48,070
-Yes, I believe you are.
-Thank you.

430
00:35:49,240 --> 00:35:51,100
-What are you doing?
-I'm doing you a favour.

431
00:35:51,440 --> 00:35:52,840
I couldn't just leave you there,
looking all pathetic.

432
00:35:53,120 --> 00:35:55,859
Take a seat. I'm gonna give you
a vaccine against viral infection

433
00:35:56,320 --> 00:35:59,580
-from Melvaran mud fleas.
-What for?

434
00:36:00,120 --> 00:36:01,980
-To give you the symptoms.
-What are you talking about?

435
00:36:02,320 --> 00:36:04,210
You're gonna start to lose vision
in your left eye.

436
00:36:04,560 --> 00:36:05,540
Yeah, I already have.

437
00:36:05,800 --> 00:36:08,080
Oh, and you're gonna get
a really bad headache and a flop sweat.

438
00:36:08,480 --> 00:36:10,270
-You call this a favour?
-Yeah. You owe me one.

439
00:36:12,760 --> 00:36:16,660
Kirk, James T. He is not cleared
for duty aboard the Enterprise.

440
00:36:17,280 --> 00:36:18,580
Medical code states the treatment

441
00:36:18,840 --> 00:36:20,520
and transport of a patient is
to be determined

442
00:36:20,840 --> 00:36:23,440
at the discretion of his
attending physician, which is me.

443
00:36:23,880 --> 00:36:25,460
So I'm taking Mr Kirk aboard.

444
00:36:25,760 --> 00:36:27,790
Or would you like to explain
to Captain Pike

445
00:36:28,160 --> 00:36:29,700
why the Enterprise warped into a crisis

446
00:36:30,000 --> 00:36:32,390
without one of its senior
medical officers?

447
00:36:32,800 --> 00:36:35,750
-As you were.
-As you were. Come on.

448
00:36:53,240 --> 00:36:56,430
-I might throw up on you.
-Jim, you've got to look at this.

449
00:36:57,880 --> 00:36:58,960
-Jim, look.
-What?

450
00:36:59,200 --> 00:37:00,069
Look.

451
00:37:54,200 --> 00:37:57,819
-We need to get you changed.
-I don't feel right. I feel like I'm leaking.

452
00:37:58,400 --> 00:38:00,680
Hell, it's that pointy-eared bastard.

453
00:38:17,240 --> 00:38:19,560
-Mr Spock.
-Captain.

454
00:38:20,000 --> 00:38:22,530
-Engineering reports ready for launch.
-Thank you.

455
00:38:22,960 --> 00:38:24,890
Ladies and gentlemen, the maiden
voyage of our newest flagship

456
00:38:25,240 --> 00:38:28,120
deserves more pomp and circumstance
than we can afford today.

457
00:38:28,600 --> 00:38:31,900
Her christening will just have to be
our reward for a safe return. Carry on.

458
00:38:33,320 --> 00:38:35,250
All decks, this is Captain Pike.
Prepare for immediate departure.

459
00:38:35,600 --> 00:38:36,680
Helm, thrusters.

460
00:38:36,920 --> 00:38:38,920
Moorings retracted, Captain.
Dock Control reports ready.

461
00:38:39,280 --> 00:38:41,100
Thrusters fired.
Separating from spacedock.

462
00:38:50,800 --> 00:38:53,540
The fleet's cleared spacedock, Captain.
All ships ready for warp.

463
00:38:54,000 --> 00:38:57,440
-Set a course for Vulcan.
-Aye-aye, Captain. Course laid in.

464
00:38:59,080 --> 00:39:01,180
Maximum warp. Punch it.

465
00:39:17,760 --> 00:39:19,300
Lieutenant,
where is Helmsman McKenna?

466
00:39:19,600 --> 00:39:22,200
He has lungworms, sir.
He couldn't report to his post.

467
00:39:22,640 --> 00:39:23,870
I'm Hikaru Sulu.

468
00:39:24,120 --> 00:39:26,960
-And you are a pilot, right?
-Very much so, sir.

469
00:39:27,440 --> 00:39:30,280
I'm not sure what's wrong here.

470
00:39:30,760 --> 00:39:34,090
-ls the parking brake on?
-No. I'll figure it out. I'm just...

471
00:39:34,640 --> 00:39:37,410
Have you disengaged
the external inertial dampener?

472
00:39:41,600 --> 00:39:43,390
-Ready for warp, sir.
-Let's punch it.

473
00:39:50,880 --> 00:39:52,180
-Where are we?
-Medical Bay.

474
00:39:52,440 --> 00:39:53,980
-This isn't worth it.
-A little suffering's good for the soul.

475
00:39:54,280 --> 00:39:55,720
-Hi! How are you?
-Come here.

476
00:39:56,000 --> 00:39:58,980
-My mouth is itchy. Is that normal?
-Well, those symptoms won't last long.

477
00:39:59,480 --> 00:40:02,110
-I'm going to give you a mild sedative.
-I wish I didn't know you.

478
00:40:02,560 --> 00:40:04,100
Don't be such an infant.

479
00:40:05,640 --> 00:40:06,970
How long is it supposed to...

480
00:40:07,760 --> 00:40:08,950
Unbelievable.

481
00:40:10,440 --> 00:40:12,470
-Engines at maximum warp, Captain.
-Russian whiz kid, what's your name?

482
00:40:12,840 --> 00:40:16,070
-Chanko? Cherpov?
-Ensign Chekov, Pavel Andreievich, sir.

483
00:40:16,600 --> 00:40:19,580
Fine, Chekov, Pavel Andreievich.
Begin ship-wide mission broadcast.

484
00:40:20,080 --> 00:40:21,520
Yes, sir. Happy to.

485
00:40:22,440 --> 00:40:25,630
Ensign authorisation code
nine-five-Wictor-Wictor-two.

486
00:40:26,160 --> 00:40:27,810
Authorisation not recognised.

487
00:40:28,120 --> 00:40:29,980
Ensign authorisation code

488
00:40:30,320 --> 00:40:33,940
nine-five-Victor-Victor-two.

489
00:40:36,760 --> 00:40:38,790
May I have your attention, please?

490
00:40:39,880 --> 00:40:44,270
At 2200 hours, telemetry detected
an anomaly in the Neutral Zone.

491
00:40:45,160 --> 00:40:47,930
What appeared to be
a lightning storm in space.

492
00:40:48,680 --> 00:40:52,609
Soon after, Starfleet received a distress
signal from the Vulcan High Command

493
00:40:53,320 --> 00:40:56,300
that their planet
was experiencing seismic activity.

494
00:40:57,200 --> 00:41:00,390
Our mission is to assess
the condition of Vulcan

495
00:41:00,920 --> 00:41:03,690
and assist in evacuations if necessary.

496
00:41:04,640 --> 00:41:08,609
We should be arriving at Vulcan within
three minutes. Thank you for your time.

497
00:41:10,720 --> 00:41:14,720
-Lightning storm.
-Jim, you're awake. How do you feel?

498
00:41:16,600 --> 00:41:18,490
-Good God, man.
-What?

499
00:41:20,920 --> 00:41:23,380
-What the hell's this?
-A reaction to the vaccine, damn it!

500
00:41:23,800 --> 00:41:25,660
Nurse Chapel,
I need 50 cc's of cortisone!

501
00:41:26,280 --> 00:41:27,470
Yes, sir!

502
00:41:29,800 --> 00:41:32,190
... appeared to be
a lightning storm in space.

503
00:41:32,600 --> 00:41:34,490
-Hey!
-We gotta stop the ship.

504
00:41:35,240 --> 00:41:38,399
Jim! I'm not kidding!
We need to keep your heart rate down!

505
00:41:39,080 --> 00:41:40,310
Computer, locate crew member Uhura.

506
00:41:40,560 --> 00:41:42,350
You know, I haven't seen a reaction
this severe since med school.

507
00:41:42,680 --> 00:41:45,350
-We're flying into a trap!
-Damn it, Jim, stand still!

508
00:41:47,080 --> 00:41:48,310
Stop it!

509
00:41:56,880 --> 00:41:58,460
-Uhura! Uhura...
-Kirk! What are you doing here?

510
00:41:58,760 --> 00:42:00,410
The transmission from the Klingon
prison planet. What exactly...

511
00:42:00,720 --> 00:42:02,370
Oh, my God,
what's wrong with your hands?

512
00:42:02,680 --> 00:42:04,290
It's... Look, who is responsible
for the Klingon attack?

513
00:42:04,600 --> 00:42:05,900
-What?
-And was the ship...

514
00:42:06,160 --> 00:42:07,069
Was the ship what?

515
00:42:07,280 --> 00:42:09,310
-What's happening to my mouth?
-You got numb tongue?

516
00:42:09,680 --> 00:42:11,330
-Numb tongue?
-I can fix that.

517
00:42:11,640 --> 00:42:13,290
-Was the ship what?
-Romulan.

518
00:42:13,600 --> 00:42:15,140
-What? I...
-Romulan.

519
00:42:15,440 --> 00:42:16,380
-Romulan?
-Yeah!

520
00:42:16,600 --> 00:42:17,650
-Yes.
-Yes?

521
00:42:17,880 --> 00:42:18,720
Damn it!

522
00:42:51,400 --> 00:42:54,170
Prod Nero. Seven Federation ships
are on their way.

523
00:42:56,680 --> 00:42:57,589
-Jim!
-What's going on?

524
00:42:57,800 --> 00:42:58,670
-Jim, come back!
-Kirk!

525
00:42:58,880 --> 00:43:00,420
-Captain! Captain Pike, sir...
-Jim, come back here!

526
00:43:00,720 --> 00:43:01,950
-...we have to stop the ship!
-Kirk, how the hell

527
00:43:02,200 --> 00:43:03,500
did you get onboard the Enterprise?

528
00:43:03,760 --> 00:43:05,230
Captain, this man's under the influence

529
00:43:05,520 --> 00:43:06,780
-of a severe reaction to a vaccine.
-Bones, please...

530
00:43:07,040 --> 00:43:08,480
He's completely delusional,
and I take full responsibility.

531
00:43:08,760 --> 00:43:09,990
Vulcan is not experiencing
a natural disaster.

532
00:43:10,240 --> 00:43:11,399
It's being attacked by Romulans.

533
00:43:11,640 --> 00:43:14,450
Romulans? Cadet Kirk, I think you've
had enough attention for one day.

534
00:43:14,920 --> 00:43:16,040
McCoy, take him back to medical.

535
00:43:16,280 --> 00:43:17,610
-We'll have words later.
-Aye, Captain.

536
00:43:17,880 --> 00:43:19,110
Look, sir, that same anomaly
that we saw today...

537
00:43:19,360 --> 00:43:20,830
Mr Kirk is not cleared
to be aboard this vessel, Captain.

538
00:43:21,120 --> 00:43:22,200
-l get it. You're a great arguer.
-By Regulations...

539
00:43:22,440 --> 00:43:23,880
-I'd love to do it again.
-...that makes him a stowaway.

540
00:43:24,160 --> 00:43:25,240
-I can remove the cadet...
-Try it!

541
00:43:25,480 --> 00:43:26,740
-Kirk...
-This cadet is trying to save the Bridge.

542
00:43:27,000 --> 00:43:29,530
By recommending a full stop mid-warp
during a rescue mission?

543
00:43:29,960 --> 00:43:31,360
It's not a rescue mission.
Listen to me, it's an attack.

544
00:43:31,640 --> 00:43:33,109
Based on what facts?

545
00:43:35,200 --> 00:43:37,620
That same anomaly, a lightning storm
in space that we saw today,

546
00:43:38,040 --> 00:43:39,690
also occurred on the day of my birth,

547
00:43:40,000 --> 00:43:42,420
before a Romulan ship
attacked the U.S.S. Kelvin.

548
00:43:42,840 --> 00:43:44,560
You know that, sir,
l read your dissertation.

549
00:43:44,880 --> 00:43:47,090
That ship, which had formidable
and advanced weaponry,

550
00:43:47,480 --> 00:43:48,920
was never seen or heard from again.

551
00:43:49,200 --> 00:43:50,850
The Kelvin attack took place
on the edge of Klingon space,

552
00:43:51,160 --> 00:43:53,509
and at 2300 hours last night,
there was an attack.

553
00:43:53,960 --> 00:43:56,840
Forty-seven Klingon warbirds
destroyed by Romulans, sir,

554
00:43:57,320 --> 00:44:00,130
and it was reported that the Romulans
were in one ship, one massive ship.

555
00:44:00,600 --> 00:44:02,950
And you know
of this Klingon attack how?

556
00:44:05,520 --> 00:44:08,360
Sir, l intercepted and translated
the message myself.

557
00:44:09,000 --> 00:44:11,100
-Kirk's report is accurate.
-We're warping into a trap, sir.

558
00:44:11,480 --> 00:44:14,080
The Romulans are waiting for us,
I promise you that.

559
00:44:15,160 --> 00:44:16,980
The cadet's logic is sound.

560
00:44:17,760 --> 00:44:19,480
And Lieutenant Uhura is unmatched
in xenolinguistics.

561
00:44:19,800 --> 00:44:21,380
We would be wise
to accept her conclusion.

562
00:44:21,680 --> 00:44:24,169
Scan Vulcan space. Check
for any transmissions in Romulan.

563
00:44:24,600 --> 00:44:27,410
Sir, I'm not sure I can distinguish
the Romulan language from Vulcan.

564
00:44:27,880 --> 00:44:29,560
What about you?
Do you speak Romulan, Cadet...

565
00:44:29,880 --> 00:44:31,210
Uhura. All three dialects, sir.

566
00:44:31,480 --> 00:44:34,080
-Uhura, relieve the lieutenant.
-Yes, sir.

567
00:44:34,680 --> 00:44:35,980
Hannity, hail the U.S.S. Truman.

568
00:44:36,240 --> 00:44:38,310
All the other ships are out of warp, sir,
and have arrived at Vulcan,

569
00:44:38,680 --> 00:44:40,569
but we seem to have lost all contact.

570
00:44:40,920 --> 00:44:43,200
Sir, ! pick up no Romulan transmission,

571
00:44:43,600 --> 00:44:47,360
-or transmission of any kind in the area.
-It's because they're being attacked.

572
00:44:51,560 --> 00:44:53,100
Shields up. Red alert.

573
00:44:55,240 --> 00:44:56,919
Arrival at Vulcan in five seconds.

574
00:44:57,800 --> 00:45:00,190
Four, three, two...

575
00:45:02,240 --> 00:45:03,430
-Emergency evasive!
-On it, sir.

576
00:45:11,880 --> 00:45:13,280
-Damage report!
-Deflector shields are holding.

577
00:45:13,560 --> 00:45:15,310
All stations! Engineer Olson, report!

578
00:45:25,280 --> 00:45:26,750
Full reverse.
Come about starboard 90 degrees.

579
00:45:27,040 --> 00:45:28,300
Drop us down underneath them, Sulu.

580
00:45:46,920 --> 00:45:48,640
Sir, there's another Federation ship!

581
00:45:48,960 --> 00:45:50,710
-Destroy it, too.
-Fire torpedoes.

582
00:45:51,040 --> 00:45:52,050
Captain, they're locking torpedoes.

583
00:45:52,280 --> 00:45:54,350
Divert auxiliary power from port nacelles
to forward shields.

584
00:46:02,160 --> 00:46:04,299
-Sulu, status report.
-Shields at 32%.

585
00:46:04,680 --> 00:46:06,710
Their weapons are powerful, sir.
We can't take another hit like that.

586
00:46:07,080 --> 00:46:07,990
Get me Starfleet Command.

587
00:46:08,200 --> 00:46:10,870
Captain, the Romulan ship has lowered
some kind of high-energy pulse device

588
00:46:11,320 --> 00:46:12,370
into the Vulcan atmosphere.

589
00:46:12,600 --> 00:46:13,900
Its signal appears to be blocking
our communications

590
00:46:14,160 --> 00:46:15,950
-and transporter abilities.
-All power to forward shields.

591
00:46:16,280 --> 00:46:17,440
Prepare to fire all weapons.

592
00:46:22,000 --> 00:46:24,170
-Weapons ready.
-Wait!

593
00:46:24,920 --> 00:46:27,090
-The hull. Magnify.
-Yes, sir.

594
00:46:32,120 --> 00:46:33,910
Captain, we're being hailed.

595
00:46:35,160 --> 00:46:36,170
Hello.

596
00:46:38,120 --> 00:46:40,580
I'm Captain Christopher Pike.
To whom am I speaking?

597
00:46:41,000 --> 00:46:42,750
Hi, Christopher. I'm Nero.

598
00:46:43,080 --> 00:46:44,620
You've declared war
against the Federation.

599
00:46:44,920 --> 00:46:47,520
Withdraw, I'll agree to arrange
a conference with Romulan leadership

600
00:46:47,960 --> 00:46:50,770
-at a neutral location.
-! do not speak for the Empire.

601
00:46:51,240 --> 00:46:52,500
We stand apart.

602
00:46:54,120 --> 00:46:57,310
As does your Vulcan crew member.
Isn't that right, Spock?

603
00:47:00,360 --> 00:47:02,680
Pardon me, I do not believe
that you and I are acquainted.

604
00:47:03,080 --> 00:47:05,360
No, we're not. Not yet.

605
00:47:06,640 --> 00:47:09,379
Spock, there’s something
! would like you to see.

606
00:47:11,200 --> 00:47:14,180
Captain Pike,
your transporter has been disabled.

607
00:47:15,200 --> 00:47:18,460
As you can see by the rest
of your armada, you have no choice.

608
00:47:19,360 --> 00:47:22,840
You will man a shuttle and come aboard
the Narada for negotiations.

609
00:47:23,880 --> 00:47:25,110
That is all.

610
00:47:33,960 --> 00:47:35,540
-He'll kill you. You know that.
-Your survival is unlikely.

611
00:47:35,840 --> 00:47:38,370
Captain, we gain nothing by diplomacy.
Going over to that ship is a mistake.

612
00:47:38,800 --> 00:47:40,270
I, too, agree.
You should rethink your strategy.

613
00:47:40,560 --> 00:47:41,960
l understand that.

614
00:47:42,920 --> 00:47:45,660
I need officers who've been trained
in advanced hand-to-hand combat.

615
00:47:46,120 --> 00:47:48,859
-I have training, sir.
-Come with me.

616
00:47:50,080 --> 00:47:52,040
Kirk, you, too.
You're not supposed to be here anyway.

617
00:47:52,400 --> 00:47:54,680
-Chekov, you have the conn.
-Aye-aye, Captain.

618
00:48:15,240 --> 00:48:16,890
Prepare the red matter.

619
00:48:18,480 --> 00:48:19,600
Yes, sir.

620
00:48:56,720 --> 00:48:58,580
Without transporters,
we can't beam off the ship,

621
00:48:58,920 --> 00:49:00,640
we can't assist Vulcan,
we can't do our job.

622
00:49:00,960 --> 00:49:05,100
Mr Kirk, Mr Sulu, Engineer Olson
will space-jump from the shuttle.

623
00:49:06,120 --> 00:49:08,370
You will land on that machine
they've lowered into the atmosphere

624
00:49:08,760 --> 00:49:11,390
that's scrambling our gear.
You'll get inside, you'll disable it,

625
00:49:11,840 --> 00:49:12,960
then you'll beam back to the ship.

626
00:49:13,200 --> 00:49:16,149
Mr Spock, I'm leaving you
in command of the Enterprise.

627
00:49:16,720 --> 00:49:18,790
Once we have transport capability
and communications back up,

628
00:49:19,160 --> 00:49:21,620
you'll contact Starfleet and report
what the hell's going on here.

629
00:49:22,040 --> 00:49:23,550
And if all else fails, fall back

630
00:49:23,840 --> 00:49:25,590
and rendezvous with the fleet
in the Laurentian system.

631
00:49:25,920 --> 00:49:27,110
Kirk, I'm promoting you to first officer.

632
00:49:27,360 --> 00:49:28,520
-What?
-Captain?

633
00:49:28,760 --> 00:49:31,320
Please, I apologise, the complexities
of human pranks escape me.

634
00:49:31,760 --> 00:49:35,620
It's not a prank, Spock.
And I'm not the Captain, you are.

635
00:49:37,160 --> 00:49:38,279
Let's go.

636
00:49:41,320 --> 00:49:43,280
Sir, after we knock out that drill,
what happens to you?

637
00:49:43,640 --> 00:49:45,640
Well, ! guess you'll have to come
and get me.

638
00:49:46,000 --> 00:49:48,070
Careful with the ship, Spock,
she's brand new.

639
00:49:59,360 --> 00:50:00,660
Dr Puri, report.

640
00:50:00,920 --> 00:50:03,340
It's McCoy.
Dr Puri was on Deck 6. He's dead.

641
00:50:05,440 --> 00:50:08,250
Then you have just inherited his
responsibility as chief medical officer.

642
00:50:08,720 --> 00:50:09,879
Yeah, tell me something I don't know.

643
00:50:11,240 --> 00:50:12,919
Shuttle 37, you're clear forward!

644
00:50:13,680 --> 00:50:16,450
Shuttle 89, U.S.S. Enterprise,
you are clear forward.

645
00:50:16,920 --> 00:50:18,950
Interval check shows
positive and steady.

646
00:50:19,880 --> 00:50:21,600
-You got the charges, right?
-Oh, yeah.

647
00:50:21,920 --> 00:50:24,310
I can't wait to kick some Romulan ass.
Right?

648
00:50:24,720 --> 00:50:26,299
-Yeah.
-Hell, yeah.

649
00:50:30,200 --> 00:50:33,220
Shuttle command, we advise
you activate your shields now.

650
00:50:45,400 --> 00:50:47,050
So what kind of combat training
do you have?

651
00:50:47,360 --> 00:50:48,520
Fencing.

652
00:50:51,800 --> 00:50:52,850
Pre-jump.

653
00:50:57,160 --> 00:51:00,109
Shuttle commander, you are clear
from U.S.S. Enterprise airspace.

654
00:51:06,720 --> 00:51:08,370
Gentlemen, we're approaching
the drop zone.

655
00:51:08,680 --> 00:51:11,210
We have one shot
to land on that platform.

656
00:51:11,680 --> 00:51:14,379
They may have defences,
so pull your chute as late as possible.

657
00:51:14,840 --> 00:51:17,300
Three, two, one.

658
00:51:19,280 --> 00:51:21,170
Remember, the Enterprise
won't be able to beam you back

659
00:51:21,520 --> 00:51:22,750
until you turn off that drill.

660
00:51:24,840 --> 00:51:25,750
Good luck.

661
00:51:46,920 --> 00:51:49,090
Away team is entering
the atmosphere, sir.

662
00:51:49,480 --> 00:51:50,670
Twenty thousand metres.

663
00:52:14,440 --> 00:52:16,330
Approaching the platform
at 5,800 metres.

664
00:52:16,680 --> 00:52:20,049
Kirk to Enterprise.
Distance to target, 5,000 metres.

665
00:52:23,200 --> 00:52:24,810
Forty-six hundred metres
from the platform.

666
00:52:25,120 --> 00:52:26,310
Forty-five hundred metres to target.

667
00:52:28,400 --> 00:52:29,630
Four thousand metres.

668
00:52:29,880 --> 00:52:31,700
-Three thousand metres.
-Three thousand metres.

669
00:52:32,040 --> 00:52:33,830
-Two thousand metres.
-Pulling chute.

670
00:52:39,640 --> 00:52:42,450
-Two thousand metres!
-Come on, pull your chute, Olson!

671
00:52:43,160 --> 00:52:45,580
No, not yet! Not yet! 1,500 metres!

672
00:52:46,000 --> 00:52:49,020
-Olson, open your chute!
-Olson, pull your chute!

673
00:52:49,520 --> 00:52:50,960
One thousand metres!

674
00:52:56,320 --> 00:52:57,190
No!

675
00:53:03,080 --> 00:53:04,130
Olson!

676
00:53:05,440 --> 00:53:06,630
Olson is gone, sir!

677
00:53:26,120 --> 00:53:27,589
Kirk has landed, sir.

678
00:55:26,440 --> 00:55:28,690
Give me your hand! Come on.

679
00:55:34,960 --> 00:55:36,540
Olson had the charges.

680
00:55:37,560 --> 00:55:38,610
I know.

681
00:55:40,880 --> 00:55:42,770
-What do we do?
-This.

682
00:55:55,280 --> 00:55:58,090
The jamming signal's gone.
Transport abilities are re-established.

683
00:55:58,560 --> 00:56:01,440
-Transporter control is reengaged, sir.
-Chekov, run gravitational sensors.

684
00:56:01,920 --> 00:56:03,150
I want to know
what they are doing to the planet.

685
00:56:03,400 --> 00:56:05,260
Aye, Commander.
Captain. Sorry. Captain.

686
00:56:10,600 --> 00:56:13,440
The drill's been sabotaged, sir,
but we have reached the planet's core.

687
00:56:13,920 --> 00:56:14,930
Launch the red matter.

688
00:56:29,480 --> 00:56:32,150
Kirk to Enterprise. They just launched
something at the planet

689
00:56:32,600 --> 00:56:33,720
through the hole they just drilled.

690
00:56:34,200 --> 00:56:35,990
-Do you copy, Enterprise?
-Yes, sir.

691
00:56:36,320 --> 00:56:37,620
-Analysing data now.
-Transporter is now operational.

692
00:56:37,880 --> 00:56:40,230
Captain, gravitational sensors
are off the scale.

693
00:56:40,640 --> 00:56:42,390
If my calculations are correct,

694
00:56:42,720 --> 00:56:47,000
they're creating a singularity
that will consume the planet.

695
00:56:49,880 --> 00:56:52,760
They're creating a black hole
at the centre of Vulcan?

696
00:56:53,240 --> 00:56:55,490
-Yes, sir.
-How long does the planet have?

697
00:56:57,800 --> 00:56:59,380
Minutes, sir. Minutes.

698
00:57:00,920 --> 00:57:02,780
Alert Vulcan Command Centre
to signal a planet-wide evacuation,

699
00:57:03,120 --> 00:57:04,279
-all channels, all frequencies.
-Spock, wait!

700
00:57:04,520 --> 00:57:06,030
-Maintain standard orbit.
-Yes, sir.

701
00:57:06,320 --> 00:57:08,070
-Where are you going?
-To evacuate the Vulcan High Council.

702
00:57:08,400 --> 00:57:10,080
They are tasked
with protecting our cultural history.

703
00:57:10,400 --> 00:57:12,190
-My parents will be among them.
-Can't you beam them out?

704
00:57:12,520 --> 00:57:14,590
It is impossible.
They will be in the katric ark.

705
00:57:14,960 --> 00:57:16,400
I must get them myself.

706
00:57:16,680 --> 00:57:18,540
-Chekov, you have the conn.
-Aye.

707
