in the Kentucky Derby,

947
01:17:55,040 --> 01:17:56,970
“you don't leave your prize stallion
in the stable.”

948
01:17:57,320 --> 01:17:58,400
A curious metaphor, Doctor,

949
01:17:58,640 --> 01:18:02,330
as a Stallion must first be broken
before it can reach its potential.

950
01:18:02,920 --> 01:18:04,850
My God, man, you could at least act
like it was a hard decision!

951
01:18:05,200 --> 01:18:06,280
l intend to assist in the effort

952
01:18:06,520 --> 01:18:08,690
to re-establish communication
with Starfleet.

953
01:18:09,120 --> 01:18:12,349
However, if crew morale is better served
by my roaming the halls weeping,

954
01:18:12,880 --> 01:18:15,410
I will gladly defer
to your medical expertise.

955
01:18:16,920 --> 01:18:18,040
Excuse me.

956
01:18:22,440 --> 01:18:23,669
Green-blooded hobgoblin.

957
01:18:59,880 --> 01:19:00,890
Hello!

958
01:19:41,920 --> 01:19:42,900
What?

959
01:19:46,960 --> 01:19:48,540
You realise how unacceptable this is?

960
01:19:48,840 --> 01:19:50,030
-Fascinating.
-What?

961
01:19:50,280 --> 01:19:51,509
Okay, I'm sure you're just
doing your job,

962
01:19:51,760 --> 01:19:53,270
but could you not have come
a wee bit sooner?

963
01:19:53,560 --> 01:19:54,610
Six months I've been here,

964
01:19:54,840 --> 01:19:57,470
living off Starfleet protein nibs
and the promise of a good meal!

965
01:19:58,000 --> 01:20:00,210
And I know exactly
what's going on here, okay?

966
01:20:00,600 --> 01:20:02,180
Punishment, isn't it? Ongoing.

967
01:20:02,480 --> 01:20:04,089
For something
that was clearly an accident.

968
01:20:04,400 --> 01:20:06,750
-You are Montgomery Scott.
-You know him?

969
01:20:07,160 --> 01:20:08,910
Aye, that's me. You're in the right place.

970
01:20:09,240 --> 01:20:11,910
Unless there's another hardworking,
equally starved Starfleet officer around.

971
01:20:12,360 --> 01:20:14,570
-Me.
-Get aff! Shut up!

972
01:20:14,960 --> 01:20:16,990
You don't eat anything!
You can eat, like, a bean,

973
01:20:17,360 --> 01:20:20,269
and you're done.
I'm talking about food. Real food.

974
01:20:20,760 --> 01:20:22,790
But you're here now, so thank you.
Where is it?

975
01:20:23,160 --> 01:20:24,769
You are, in fact, the Mr Scott

976
01:20:25,080 --> 01:20:26,940
who postulated
the theory of transwarp beaming.

977
01:20:27,280 --> 01:20:30,050
That's what I'm talking about.
How do you think I wound up here?

978
01:20:30,520 --> 01:20:31,780
l had a little debate with my instructor

979
01:20:32,040 --> 01:20:35,519
on the issue of relativistic physics
and how it pertains to subspace travel.

980
01:20:36,080 --> 01:20:39,380
He seemed to think that the range of
transporting something like a grapefruit

981
01:20:39,920 --> 01:20:41,180
was limited to about 100 miles.

982
01:20:41,440 --> 01:20:43,719
I told him that I could not only
beam a grapefruit from one planet

983
01:20:44,120 --> 01:20:45,800
to the adjacent planet
in the same system,

984
01:20:46,120 --> 01:20:47,519
which is easy, by the way,

985
01:20:47,800 --> 01:20:48,990
could do it with a life-form.

986
01:20:49,240 --> 01:20:51,940
So, I tested it on Admiral Archer's
prize beagle.

987
01:20:52,400 --> 01:20:55,450
-I know that dog. What happened to it?
-I'll tell you when it reappears.

988
01:20:55,960 --> 01:20:57,540
I don't know. I do feel guilty about that.

989
01:20:57,840 --> 01:21:00,300
What if I told you
that your transwarp theory was correct,

990
01:21:00,720 --> 01:21:03,460
that it is indeed possible to beam onto
a ship that is travelling at warp speed?

991
01:21:03,920 --> 01:21:06,020
I think if that equation had been
discovered, I'd have heard about it.

992
01:21:06,400 --> 01:21:07,980
The reason you haven't heard of it,
Mr Scott,

993
01:21:08,280 --> 01:21:10,670
is because you haven't discovered it yet.

994
01:21:15,760 --> 01:21:18,600
-Are you from the future?
-Yeah, he is. I'm not.

995
01:21:19,720 --> 01:21:21,930
Well, that's brilliant.
Do they still have sandwiches there?

996
01:21:22,400 --> 01:21:23,799
Well, she's a wee bit dodgy.

997
01:21:24,080 --> 01:21:27,340
Shield emitters are totally banjaxed,
as well as a few other things.

998
01:21:27,880 --> 01:21:28,820
On youse go.

999
01:21:29,040 --> 01:21:31,600
So the Enterprise has had
its maiden voyage, has it?

1000
01:21:32,040 --> 01:21:33,440
She is one well-endowed lady.

1001
01:21:33,720 --> 01:21:35,440
I'd like to get my hands
on her ample nacelles,

1002
01:21:35,760 --> 01:21:38,080
if you'll pardon
the engineering parlance.

1003
01:21:39,360 --> 01:21:41,610
Except, the thing is,
even if I believed you, right,

1004
01:21:42,000 --> 01:21:44,980
where you're from, what I've done,
which I don't, by the way,

1005
01:21:45,480 --> 01:21:47,549
you're still talking about
beaming aboard the Enterprise

1006
01:21:47,920 --> 01:21:50,340
while she's travelling faster than light
without a proper receiving pad.

1007
01:21:50,760 --> 01:21:53,110
Get off there! It's not a climbing frame.

1008
01:21:53,520 --> 01:21:57,450
The notion of transwarp beaming is like
trying to hit a bullet with a smaller bullet

1009
01:21:58,080 --> 01:22:00,500
whilst wearing a blindfold,
riding a horse.

1010
01:22:00,920 --> 01:22:01,790
What's that?

1011
01:22:02,000 --> 01:22:04,600
Your equation
for achieving transwarp beaming.

1012
01:22:07,120 --> 01:22:08,420
Get out of it.

1013
01:22:12,360 --> 01:22:13,299
Imagine that!

1014
01:22:13,520 --> 01:22:16,220
It never occurred to me to think of space
as the thing that was moving.

1015
01:22:16,680 --> 01:22:18,610
You're coming with us, right?

1016
01:22:20,440 --> 01:22:23,530
-No, Jim. That is not my destiny.
-Your...

1017
01:22:24,920 --> 01:22:26,740
He... The other Spock
is not gonna believe me.

1018
01:22:27,080 --> 01:22:28,019
Only you can explain
what the hell's happened.

1019
01:22:28,240 --> 01:22:30,559
Under no circumstances
can he be made aware of my existence.

1020
01:22:30,960 --> 01:22:31,870
You must promise me this.

1021
01:22:32,080 --> 01:22:34,710
You're telling me I can't tell you
that I'm following your own orders?

1022
01:22:35,160 --> 01:22:38,180
-Why not? What happens?
-Jim, this is one rule you cannot break.

1023
01:22:38,680 --> 01:22:41,660
To stop Nero, you alone
must take command of your ship.

1024
01:22:42,160 --> 01:22:44,760
-How? Over your dead body?
-Preferably not.

1025
01:22:45,200 --> 01:22:47,730
However, there is
Starfleet Regulation 619.

1026
01:22:48,160 --> 01:22:50,830
Six-one-nine states
that any command officer

1027
01:22:51,280 --> 01:22:53,880
who's emotionally compromised
by the mission at hand

1028
01:22:54,320 --> 01:22:56,000
must resign said command.

1029
01:22:58,360 --> 01:23:01,839
So, you're saying that I have
to emotionally compromise you guys.

1030
01:23:02,400 --> 01:23:04,929
Jim, I just lost my planet.

1031
01:23:06,400 --> 01:23:08,889
I can tell you,
lam emotionally compromised.

1032
01:23:10,120 --> 01:23:12,470
What you must do is get me to show it.

1033
01:23:12,880 --> 01:23:15,860
Aye, then, laddie.
Live or die. Let's get this over with.

1034
01:23:20,520 --> 01:23:23,080
No, go. You cannae come with me.
Go on.

1035
01:23:25,120 --> 01:23:27,470
You know, coming back in time,
changing history,

1036
01:23:28,280 --> 01:23:29,509
that's cheating.

1037
01:23:31,800 --> 01:23:33,730
A trick I learned from an old friend.

1038
01:23:42,520 --> 01:23:44,800
Live long and prosper.

1039
01:24:04,440 --> 01:24:05,669
Mr Scott!

1040
01:24:10,760 --> 01:24:12,690
Mr Scott, can you hear me?

1041
01:24:20,240 --> 01:24:21,639
Hold on a second!

1042
01:24:22,640 --> 01:24:23,510
Oh, no.

1043
01:24:27,080 --> 01:24:28,450
Don't worry, I...

1044
01:24:39,000 --> 01:24:39,870
No. No!

1045
01:24:59,040 --> 01:25:01,140
Turbine release vaive activated.

1046
01:25:07,840 --> 01:25:09,940
You all right? You all right?

1047
01:25:12,240 --> 01:25:14,309
My head's buzzing and I'm soaked,
but otherwise I'm fine.

1048
01:25:14,800 --> 01:25:19,790
Captain Spock! Detecting unauthorised
access to Water Turbine Control Board.

1049
01:25:20,560 --> 01:25:21,540
Bring up the video.

1050
01:25:25,720 --> 01:25:27,120
Security, seal the Engineering Deck.

1051
01:25:27,400 --> 01:25:29,820
We have intruders in Turbine Section 3.

1052
01:25:30,280 --> 01:25:31,219
Set phasers to stun.

1053
01:25:42,880 --> 01:25:44,140
-Halt!
-No, no!

1054
01:25:48,080 --> 01:25:50,470
Come with me, cupcake!

1055
01:25:58,720 --> 01:25:59,630
-Who are you?
-I'm with him.

1056
01:25:59,840 --> 01:26:01,800
-He's with me.
-We are travelling at warp speed.

1057
01:26:02,160 --> 01:26:03,490
How did you manage
to beam aboard this ship?

1058
01:26:03,760 --> 01:26:04,810
Well, you're the genius,
you figure it out.

1059
01:26:05,040 --> 01:26:07,670
As acting captain of this vessel,
l order you to answer the question.

1060
01:26:08,120 --> 01:26:10,680
Well, I'm not telling, Acting Captain.

1061
01:26:11,520 --> 01:26:12,390
What, did...

1062
01:26:12,600 --> 01:26:15,200
That doesn't frustrate you, does it?
My lack of cooperation?

1063
01:26:15,640 --> 01:26:17,810
-That doesn't make you angry.
-Are you a member of Starfleet?

1064
01:26:18,200 --> 01:26:20,200
I... Yes. Can I get a towel, please?

1065
01:26:20,560 --> 01:26:22,420
Under penalty of court martial,
l order you to explain to me

1066
01:26:22,760 --> 01:26:24,720
how you were able to beam
aboard this ship while moving at warp.

1067
01:26:25,080 --> 01:26:26,309
-Well...
-Don't answer him.

1068
01:26:26,560 --> 01:26:28,000
You will answer me.

1069
01:26:29,880 --> 01:26:32,830
-I'd rather not take sides.
-What is it with you, Spock?

1070
01:26:35,040 --> 01:26:37,070
Your planet was just destroyed,
your mother murdered,

1071
01:26:37,440 --> 01:26:40,070
-and you're not even upset.
-If you are presuming

1072
01:26:40,520 --> 01:26:43,010
that these experiences in any way
impede my ability to command this ship,

1073
01:26:43,440 --> 01:26:44,910
-you are mistaken.
-And yet, you are the one

1074
01:26:45,200 --> 01:26:47,590
who said fear was necessary
for command.

1075
01:26:48,000 --> 01:26:50,880
I mean, did you see his ship?
Did you see what he did?

1076
01:26:51,760 --> 01:26:53,510
-Yes, of course I did.
-So are you afraid or aren't you?

1077
01:26:53,840 --> 01:26:55,730
I will not allow you to lecture me
about the merits of emotion.

1078
01:26:56,080 --> 01:26:57,940
-Then why don't you stop me?
-Step away from me, Mr Kirk.

1079
01:26:58,280 --> 01:27:01,050
What is it like not to feel anger?
Or heartbreak?

1080
01:27:02,040 --> 01:27:03,019
Or the need to stop at nothing

1081
01:27:03,240 --> 01:27:04,920
to avenge the death
of the woman who gave birth to you?

1082
01:27:05,280 --> 01:27:06,889
-Back away from me.
-You feel nothing!

1083
01:27:07,200 --> 01:27:09,019
It must not even compute for you.

1084
01:27:10,000 --> 01:27:10,910
You never loved her!

1085
01:27:35,040 --> 01:27:36,019
Spock!

1086
01:28:12,120 --> 01:28:14,260
Doctor, 1 am no longer fit for duty.

1087
01:28:14,920 --> 01:28:16,250
I hereby relinquish my command,

1088
01:28:16,520 --> 01:28:19,930
based on the fact that have been
emotionally compromised.

1089
01:28:20,480 --> 01:28:23,080
Please note the time and date
in the ship's log.

1090
01:28:48,280 --> 01:28:51,300
I like this ship! You know, it's exciting!

1091
01:28:54,360 --> 01:28:55,620
Well, congratulations, Jim.

1092
01:28:55,880 --> 01:28:59,530
Now we've got no captain, and
no goddamn first officer to replace him.

1093
01:29:01,040 --> 01:29:02,019
Yeah, we do.

1094
01:29:02,720 --> 01:29:04,890
-What?
-Pike made him first officer.

1095
01:29:05,280 --> 01:29:07,910
-You gotta be kidding me.
-Thanks for the support.

1096
01:29:11,080 --> 01:29:14,030
I sure hope you know
what you're doing, Captain.

1097
01:29:16,120 --> 01:29:17,349
So dol.

1098
01:29:21,920 --> 01:29:23,950
Attention, crew of the Enterprise.
This is James Kirk.

1099
01:29:25,800 --> 01:29:29,310
Mr Spock has resigned commission
and advanced me to acting captain.

1100
01:29:30,240 --> 01:29:33,080
1 know you were all expecting
to regroup with the fleet,

1101
01:29:33,560 --> 01:29:35,560
but I'm ordering a pursuit course
of the enemy ship to Earth.

1102
01:29:35,920 --> 01:29:38,660
! want all departments at battle stations
and ready in 10 minutes.

1103
01:29:39,440 --> 01:29:42,559
Either we're going down or they are.

1104
01:29:44,520 --> 01:29:45,570
Kirk out.

1105
01:29:52,880 --> 01:29:54,460
Speak your mind, Spock.

1106
01:29:57,480 --> 01:29:58,919
That would be unwise.

1107
01:29:59,760 --> 01:30:02,640
What is necessary is never unwise.

1108
01:30:04,280 --> 01:30:07,019
lam as conflicted
as I once was as a child.

1109
01:30:09,240 --> 01:30:11,630
You will always be a child of two worlds.

1110
01:30:13,640 --> 01:30:15,250
l am grateful for this.

1111
01:30:17,400 --> 01:30:18,559
And for you.

1112
01:30:20,600 --> 01:30:23,340
I feel anger
for the one who took Mother's life.

1113
01:30:25,040 --> 01:30:26,900
An anger I cannot control.

1114
01:30:31,200 --> 01:30:35,410
I believe that she would say,

1115
01:30:37,480 --> 01:30:38,809
"Do not try to.”

1116
01:30:40,280 --> 01:30:44,420
You asked me once
why I married your mother.

1117
01:30:48,840 --> 01:30:50,700
I married her because I loved her.

1118
01:30:58,800 --> 01:31:01,120
Whatever the case, we need
to get aboard Nero's ship undetected.

1119
01:31:01,520 --> 01:31:03,550
We can't just go in there guns blazing,
Jim, not with their technology.

1120
01:31:03,920 --> 01:31:05,740
I'm telling you, the math doesn't support
what you're suggesting.

1121
01:31:06,080 --> 01:31:07,870
-Captain Kirk. Captain Kirk!
-Yes, Mr Chekov. What is it?

1122
01:31:08,200 --> 01:31:09,990
Based on the Narada’s course
from Vulcan,

1123
01:31:10,320 --> 01:31:13,059
I have projected that Nero
will travel past Saturn.

1124
01:31:13,520 --> 01:31:16,290
Like you said, we need to stay invisible
to Nero or he'll destroy us.

1125
01:31:16,760 --> 01:31:18,720
If Mr Scott can get us to warp factor 4,

1126
01:31:19,080 --> 01:31:23,010
and if we drop out of warp behind
one of Saturn's moons, say, Titan,

1127
01:31:23,640 --> 01:31:25,850
the magnetic distortion
from the planet's rings

1128
01:31:26,240 --> 01:31:28,099
will make us invisible to Nero's sensors.

1129
01:31:28,440 --> 01:31:30,440
From there,
as long as the drill is not actuated,

1130
01:31:30,800 --> 01:31:33,500
-we can beam aboard the enemy ship.
-Aye, that might work.

1131
01:31:34,520 --> 01:31:35,890
Wait a minute, kid. How old are you?

1132
01:31:36,160 --> 01:31:38,440
-Seventeen, sir.
-Oh, good, he's 17.

1133
01:31:38,840 --> 01:31:40,240
Doctor.

1134
01:31:40,520 --> 01:31:43,400
Mr Chekov is correct.
I can confirm his telemetry.

1135
01:31:44,120 --> 01:31:45,800
If Mr Sulu is able
to manoeuvre us into position,

1136
01:31:46,120 --> 01:31:48,440
I can beam aboard Nero's ship,
steal back the black hole device

1137
01:31:48,840 --> 01:31:51,160
and, if possible,
bring back Captain Pike.

1138
01:31:51,560 --> 01:31:53,840
I won't allow you to do that, Mr Spock.

1139
01:31:54,240 --> 01:31:56,800
Romulans and Vulcans
share a common ancestry.

1140
01:31:57,240 --> 01:31:58,960
Our cultural similarities
will make it easier for me

1141
01:31:59,280 --> 01:32:01,950
to access the ship's computer
to locate the device.

1142
01:32:03,600 --> 01:32:05,280
Also, my mother was human,

1143
01:32:05,600 --> 01:32:08,130
which makes Earth
the only home I have left.

1144
01:32:14,440 --> 01:32:16,230
Then I'm coming with you.

1145
01:32:16,560 --> 01:32:19,970
I would cite Regulation,
but I know you will simply ignore it.

1146
01:32:22,120 --> 01:32:24,470
See? We are
getting to know each other.

1147
01:32:40,120 --> 01:32:41,099
Prepare the drill.

1148
01:32:56,800 --> 01:33:01,470
All stop in three, two, one.

1149
01:33:07,440 --> 01:33:09,610
Give me one-quarter impulse burst
for five seconds.

1150
01:33:10,000 --> 01:33:11,580
I'll do the rest with thrusters.
On my mark.

1151
01:33:11,880 --> 01:33:13,770
-Aye.
-Fire.

1152
01:33:40,160 --> 01:33:42,480
Transporter Room.
We are in position above Titan.

1153
01:33:42,880 --> 01:33:44,950
Really? Fine job, Mr Sulu. Well done.

1154
01:33:46,360 --> 01:33:49,549
-How are we, Scotty?
-Unbelievably, sir, the ship is in position.

1155
01:33:53,040 --> 01:33:54,830
Whatever happens, Mr Sulu,

1156
01:33:55,160 --> 01:33:56,599
if you think you have
the tactical advantage,

1157
01:33:56,880 --> 01:33:59,900
you fire on that ship, even if we're still
onboard. That's an order.

1158
01:34:01,800 --> 01:34:02,780
Yes, sir.

1159
01:34:03,000 --> 01:34:06,370
Otherwise we'll contact the Enterprise
when we're ready to be beamed back.

1160
01:34:06,960 --> 01:34:07,970
Good luck.

1161
01:34:20,520 --> 01:34:22,980
-I will be back.
-You better be.

1162
01:34:25,040 --> 01:34:27,570
-I'll be monitoring your frequency.
-Thank you, Nyota.

1163
01:34:44,040 --> 01:34:46,390
-So her first name's Nyota?
-Il have no comment on the matter.

1164
01:34:46,800 --> 01:34:48,380
Okey-dokey, then,
if there's any common sense

1165
01:34:48,680 --> 01:34:49,760
in the design of the enemy ship,

1166
01:34:50,000 --> 01:34:51,650
I should be putting you
somewhere in the Cargo Bay.

1167
01:34:51,960 --> 01:34:54,240
-Shouldn't be a soul in sight.
-Energise.

1168
01:35:36,080 --> 01:35:38,080
Captain, we have Starfleet officers
aboard the ship.

1169
01:35:38,720 --> 01:35:40,510
-One of them is Vulcan.
-No.

1170
01:35:45,320 --> 01:35:46,230
Ayel!

1171
01:36:00,520 --> 01:36:01,530
I'll cover you.

1172
01:36:02,120 --> 01:36:03,730
-Are you certain?
-Yeah, I got you.

1173
01:36:23,000 --> 01:36:25,770
Do you know where it is?
The black hole device.

1174
01:36:27,960 --> 01:36:29,360
And Captain Pike.

1175
01:36:51,320 --> 01:36:52,370
Move!

1176
01:36:53,000 --> 01:36:54,750
They have activated the drill.

1177
01:36:56,120 --> 01:36:57,519
Communication and transport
are inoperative.

1178
01:36:57,800 --> 01:36:59,030
Sulu, please tell me you have them.

1179
01:36:59,280 --> 01:37:00,679
Otherwise we won't be able
to beam them back.

1180
01:37:00,960 --> 01:37:02,290
Kirk and Spock are on their own now.

1181
01:37:20,920 --> 01:37:22,080
l foresee a complication.

1182
01:37:22,320 --> 01:37:24,530
The design of their ship is far
more advanced than I had anticipated.

1183
01:37:24,920 --> 01:37:27,450
Voice print and face recognition
analysis enabled.

1184
01:37:27,880 --> 01:37:29,670
Weicome back, Ambassador Spock.

1185
01:37:30,000 --> 01:37:31,300
Wow, that's weird.

1186
01:37:32,520 --> 01:37:34,940
Computer, what is
your manufacturing origin?

1187
01:37:35,360 --> 01:37:39,120
Stardate 2387. Commissioned
by the Vulcan Science Academy.

1188
01:37:42,440 --> 01:37:44,610
It appears that you have been keeping
important information from me.

1189
01:37:45,000 --> 01:37:46,720
You're gonna be able
to fly this thing, right?

1190
01:37:47,040 --> 01:37:49,110
Something tells me I already have.

1191
01:37:49,960 --> 01:37:51,290
-Good luck.
-Jim.

1192
01:37:52,600 --> 01:37:55,410
The statistical likelihood that our plan
will succeed is less than 4.3%.

1193
01:37:55,880 --> 01:37:57,630
-It'll work.
-In the event that I do not return,

1194
01:37:57,960 --> 01:37:59,640
-please tell Lieutenant Uhura...
-Spock!

1195
01:37:59,960 --> 01:38:01,400
It'll work.

1196
01:38:11,000 --> 01:38:12,260
Fascinating.

1197
01:38:20,680 --> 01:38:22,400
Start-up sequence initiated.

1198
01:39:05,080 --> 01:39:06,830
Nero, order your men to disable the drill
or I will...

1199
01:39:17,280 --> 01:39:19,809
I know your face from Earth's history.

1200
01:40:03,400 --> 01:40:06,379
James T. Kirk was considered
to be a great man.

1201
01:40:06,880 --> 01:40:08,880
He went on to captain
the U.S.S. Enterprise.

1202
01:40:09,240 --> 01:40:10,360
But that was another life.

1203
01:40:11,320 --> 01:40:13,880
A life I will deprive you of,
just like I did your father.

1204
01:40:45,520 --> 01:40:49,100
Captain Nero. The Vulcan ship has been
taken. The drill has been destroyed.

1205
01:40:50,000 --> 01:40:50,870
Spock!

1206
01:40:52,680 --> 01:40:53,980
Spock!

1207
01:41:11,080 --> 01:41:12,269
-Open a channel.
-Yes, sir!

1208
01:41:14,160 --> 01:41:16,650
Spock. I knew I should have killed you
when I had the chance.

1209
01:41:17,200 --> 01:41:18,990
I hereby confiscate
this illegally obtained ship

1210
01:41:19,320 --> 01:41:20,259
and order you to surrender your vessel.

1211
01:41:20,600 --> 01:41:22,280
-No terms. No deals.
-That ship, take it out.

1212
01:41:22,600 --> 01:41:23,610
Sir, if you ignite the red matter,

1213
01:41:23,840 --> 01:41:25,070
-you'll destroy...
-I want Spock dead now!

1214
01:41:40,560 --> 01:41:42,100
-He went to warp, sir.
-Go after him!

1215
01:41:42,400 --> 01:41:43,450
Yes, sir!

1216
01:42:12,520 --> 01:42:15,080
Your species is even weaker
than I expected.

1217
01:42:16,760 --> 01:42:18,550
-I can't...
-You can't what?

1218
01:42:18,920 --> 01:42:20,220
You can't even speak.

1219
01:42:22,880 --> 01:42:25,200
-What?
-I got your gun.

1220
01:42:51,120 --> 01:42:52,059
What's he doing?

1221
01:42:52,600 --> 01:42:55,060
Ambassador Spock,
you are on a collision course.

1222
01:42:56,120 --> 01:42:56,990
Fire everything!

1223
01:43:04,160 --> 01:43:07,740
Incoming missiles. If the ship is hit,
the red matter will be ignited.

1224
01:43:08,320 --> 01:43:09,509
Understood.

1225
01:43:15,720 --> 01:43:17,020
Captain, I've picked up another ship!

1226
01:43:38,080 --> 01:43:40,750
-What are you doing here?
-Just following orders.

1227
01:44:00,160 --> 01:44:01,099
Enterprise, now!

1228
01:44:23,680 --> 01:44:25,150
Nice timing, Scotty!

1229
01:44:26,240 --> 01:44:29,570
I've never beamed three people
from two targets onto one pad before!

1230
01:44:30,120 --> 01:44:31,700
-Jim!
-Bones!

1231
01:44:32,000 --> 01:44:33,370
I got him.

1232
01:44:35,640 --> 01:44:36,550
That was pretty good!

1233
01:44:37,920 --> 01:44:40,660
Captain, the enemy ship is losing
power! Their shields are down, sir.

1234
01:44:41,120 --> 01:44:42,309
-Hail them now.
-Aye.

1235
01:45:16,200 --> 01:45:18,620
This is Captain James T. Kirk
of the U.S.S. Enterprise.

1236
01:45:19,360 --> 01:45:20,519
Your ship is compromised.

1237
01:45:20,760 --> 01:45:22,860
Too close to the singularity
to survive without assistance,

1238
01:45:23,240 --> 01:45:24,780
which we are willing to provide.

1239
01:45:28,200 --> 01:45:30,230
-Captain, what are you doing?
-Showing them compassion

1240
01:45:30,600 --> 01:45:32,040
may be the only way
to earn peace with Romulus.

1241
01:45:32,320 --> 01:45:34,880
It's logic, Spock.
I thought you'd like that.

1242
01:45:35,320 --> 01:45:37,599
No, not really. Not this time.

1243
01:45:38,000 --> 01:45:41,790
! would rather suffer the end of Romulus
a thousand times.

1244
01:45:42,400 --> 01:45:45,980
! would rather die in agony
than accept assistance from you.

1245
01:45:46,560 --> 01:45:48,070
You got it.

1246
01:45:48,360 --> 01:45:50,780
-Arm phasers. Fire everything we've got.
-Yes, sir.

1247
01:46:34,440 --> 01:46:36,370
-Sulu, let's go home.
-Yes, sir!

1248
01:46:47,520 --> 01:46:49,240
-Why aren't we at warp?
-We are, sir.

1249
01:46:49,560 --> 01:46:51,420
Kirk to Engineering.
Get us out of here, Scotty.

1250
01:46:51,760 --> 01:46:52,880
You bet your ass, Captain!

1251
01:46:56,560 --> 01:46:58,280
Captain, we're caught in the gravity well!
It's got us!

1252
01:46:58,600 --> 01:47:01,550
-Go to maximum warp! Push it!
-I'm giving her all she's got, Captain!

1253
01:47:10,920 --> 01:47:12,150
All she's got isn't good enough!

1254
01:47:12,400 --> 01:47:15,240
-What else you got?
-Okay, if we eject the core and detonate,

1255
01:47:15,720 --> 01:47:16,800
the blast could be enough
to push us away.

1256
01:47:17,040 --> 01:47:18,019
I cannae promise anything, though!

1257
01:47:21,640 --> 01:47:22,870
Do it, do it, do it!

1258
01:47:24,200 --> 01:47:25,740
-Clear the area! Go!
-Yes, sir!

1259
01:48:49,920 --> 01:48:51,250
Father!

1260
01:48:59,440 --> 01:49:00,950
lam not our father.

1261
01:49:08,480 --> 01:49:12,410
There are so few Vulcans left.
We cannot afford to ignore each other.

1262
01:49:15,960 --> 01:49:16,940
Then why did you send Kirk aboard

1263
01:49:17,160 --> 01:49:18,769
when you alone
could have explained the truth?

1264
01:49:19,080 --> 01:49:21,990
Because you needed each other.
I could not deprive you

1265
01:49:22,480 --> 01:49:24,730
of the revelation of all
that you could accomplish together,

1266
01:49:25,120 --> 01:49:29,470
of a friendship that will define you both
in ways you cannot yet realise.

1267
01:49:31,920 --> 01:49:33,710
How did you persuade him
to keep your secret?

1268
01:49:34,040 --> 01:49:36,880
He inferred that universe-ending
paradoxes would ensue

1269
01:49:37,360 --> 01:49:39,389
-should he break his promise.
-You lied.

1270
01:49:41,040 --> 01:49:42,860
I... lL implied.

1271
01:49:43,600 --> 01:49:45,320
-A gamble.
-An act of faith.

1272
01:49:46,600 --> 01:49:49,300
One I hope that you'll repeat
in the future in Starfleet.

1273
01:49:49,760 --> 01:49:51,130
In the face of extinction, it is only logical

1274
01:49:51,400 --> 01:49:53,679
l resign my Starfleet commission
and help rebuild our race.

1275
01:49:54,080 --> 01:49:56,010
And yet,
you can be in two places at once.

1276
01:49:57,520 --> 01:49:59,840
l urge you to remain in Starfleet.

1277
01:50:00,560 --> 01:50:04,210
I have already located a suitable planet
on which to establish a Vulcan colony.

1278
01:50:04,800 --> 01:50:07,960
Spock, in this case, do yourself a favour.

1279
01:50:09,840 --> 01:50:12,580
Put aside logic. Do what feels right.

1280
01:50:18,600 --> 01:50:21,720
Since my customary farewell
would appear oddly self-serving,

1281
01:50:22,240 --> 01:50:23,290
I shall simply say

1282
01:50:24,440 --> 01:50:25,669
good luck.

1283
01:50:36,280 --> 01:50:39,400
This assembly calls Captain
James Tiberius Kirk.

1284
01:50:40,440 --> 01:50:43,320
Your inspirational valour and
supreme dedication to your comrades

1285
01:50:43,800 --> 01:50:46,050
is in keeping with
the highest traditions of service,

1286
01:50:46,440 --> 01:50:50,509
and reflect utmost credit to yourself,
your crew and the Federation.

1287
01:50:52,080 --> 01:50:54,570
It is my honour to award you
with this commendation.

1288
01:50:59,400 --> 01:51:01,080
By Starfleet Order 28455,

1289
01:51:01,400 --> 01:51:04,839
you are hereby directed to report
to Admiral Pike, U.S.S. Enterprise,

1290
01:51:05,400 --> 01:51:06,839
for duty as his relief.

1291
01:51:15,600 --> 01:51:17,040
I relieve you, sir.

1292
01:51:17,640 --> 01:51:19,180
lam relieved.

1293
01:51:21,120 --> 01:51:23,290
-Thank you, sir.
-Congratulations, Captain.

1294
01:51:25,440 --> 01:51:27,019
Your father would be proud.

1295
01:51:55,480 --> 01:51:56,879
Thrusters on full.

1296
01:51:57,640 --> 01:51:59,990
Manoeuvring thrusters and
impulse engines at your command, sir.

1297
01:52:00,440 --> 01:52:02,650
Weapons systems and shields
on standby.

1298
01:52:03,040 --> 01:52:05,250
Dock Control reports ready, Captain.

1299
01:52:09,880 --> 01:52:12,270
Bones! Buckle up.

1300
01:52:16,960 --> 01:52:18,220
Scotty, how we doing?

1301
01:52:18,480 --> 01:52:20,730
Dilithium chamber's
at maximum, Captain.

1302
01:52:22,040 --> 01:52:23,230
Get down!

1303
01:52:25,320 --> 01:52:27,809
Mr Sulu, prepare to engage thrusters.

1304
01:52:31,040 --> 01:52:33,070
Permission to come aboard, Captain.

1305
01:52:33,720 --> 01:52:35,190
Permission granted.

1306
01:52:36,120 --> 01:52:37,870
As you have yet to select a first officer,

1307
01:52:38,200 --> 01:52:40,800
respectfully 1 would like to submit
my candidacy.

1308
01:52:41,680 --> 01:52:44,560
Should you desire,
I can provide character references.

1309
01:52:45,400 --> 01:52:47,330
It would be my honour, Commander.

1310
01:52:51,120 --> 01:52:53,190
Manoeuvring thrusters, Mr Sulu.

1311
01:52:55,120 --> 01:52:56,730
Thrusters on standby.

1312
01:52:57,040 --> 01:52:58,970
-Take us out.
-Aye-aye, Captain.

1313
01:53:04,000 --> 01:53:06,740
Space, the final frontier.

1314
01:53:08,840 --> 01:53:11,790
These are the voyages
of the Starship Enterprise.

1315
01:53:13,160 --> 01:53:16,389
Her ongoing mission,
to explore strange new worlds,

1316
01:53:17,560 --> 01:53:20,790
to seek out new life-forms
and new civilizations,

1317
01:53:21,640 --> 01:53:25,500
to boldly go
where no one has gone before.

